caption: TEN Sushi has been my dine-in/take-out/delivery/special treat spot for years. Unfortunately, last evening's delivery was sub-par at best. We ordered from their website to save the restaurant from being charged fees. The site uses abbreviations that cause a guessing game of what you might be ordering. I was alerted that my location was out of their vicinity. I called and was rudely told to ignore and just order. My order disappeared and I had to retake all steps in ordering. Lack of presentation, quality and the size of rolls have significantly decreased. Our rolls were haphazardly jammed packed into one container with the bare minimum of not-so-fresh ginger, and wasabi. The edame was overcooked as well. Good news: Hit sake! Our delivery was made in a timely fashion. Maybe I will try TEN Sushi post-Covid.
Had a fantastic experience in this spot with my wife. The food comes rapidly and the customer service is just excellent. Prices are fair.
Good food. Great service...

I used to LOVE this place and felt like the quality was truly great. Their tempura was especially delicious. Unfortunately, our last few experiences were sub-par to say the least. I have continually given them the benefit of the doubt but our last take-out order was just so sad. My husband picked up the food on Wednesday (10.28) at 5pm and brought it home.  Sushi was fine, nothing to complain about.  We ordered TWO servings of mixed vegetable Tempura did have not eggplant, onions, or taro. The green beans were all mushed together and there was a total of 6 pieces for TWO servings which was super disappointing.  The seaweed salad used to be so good and now its just that generic neon stuff you get from big bins. Another disappointment.  But the worst was the Salmon.. they used to cook it well and use fresh vegetables. This time around it was strips of frozen salmon drenched in store-bought teriyaki with frozen vegetables. We threw it out.  I used to LOVE this place but its truly lost all the care put into dishes and the quality is no longer worth the price. I hope they will return to using better ingredients, it was such a wonderful place. For now I'll pass.
Best octopus 🐙 and I love TEN sushi 🍣
Good neighborhood sushi place. Has a few tables outside for dining.
Brings a variety of different types of sushi at an affordable price with friendly staff
Great lunch special!

I come to this superb place often because I love the good air that is characterizes this place. The personel is highly attentive and well trained. The service is awfully rapid. Also, the food you eat is great. I have been there often and I was always satisfied. The expense is reasobable. I highly suggest this place to my friends and family.
Great sushi, fantastic service.
Delicious sushi, very reasonably priced, great service- they even brought us warm towelettes to clean our hands which was a very nice touch
Great service food is delicious and get the souffle.... Kids loved it.

The Perfect Match roll was delicious.  The duck spring roll was not.  The shrimp tempura roll was good.  The tempura vegetables were also quite good.  Interesting cocktail menu, but we didn't try any on this visit.  Decor was nice.  We'd definitely return.

Any sushi worth having isn't going to be a steal. Pricey but amazing food every time, dining in, take out and delivery. Vegan friendly and gluten free friendly. My favorite splurge place in the slope.
NOT genuine Japanese, run by Chinese owner, chef and staff. Food as not that bad, but just about average or slightly below... A typical NYC run-of-the-mill deal...
Great food, attentive service.
The food took forever, and they waited so long to tell us that they were out of what we ordered. The food is okay but nothing great
I eat here a lot since I work nearby. I like how their service is always good and they keep the spot neat regularly. Pricing is affordable and they serve large portions.
Basically everything is amazing here
Great food at lunch for 12$
Very good @@
Very good sushi, excellent value. The fish is always tasty and the rolls are fresh, the rice is also tasty

I had just come straight from LGA and this place was the nearest to where I was staying and we were impressed with both the sushi and drinks. We had the classic mojito and something with honeydew -- the latter was unbelievable. Highly recommend the Tokyo roll, golden dragon roll and spicy crunchy salmon. Nice ambience and decent service.
Very popular with good reason. Always beautifully presented and tasty. Good sized portions and healthy options. One of our favorite Japanese places to eat in the neighborhood.
Food was good but expensive
Cut above; great service.
Yummy tuna dumpling!
Carefully and imaginatively prepared dishes in an elegant setting. Outdoor seating is also available.
Hey this is Miriam from the Brklyn Agency saying Hi and it is a real pleasure workung with you guys!!!!!
Great service, great food all in a nice atmosphere. Very artistic food presentation too.
I love sushi.
Great food as always.
The sashmi was desplayed nicely. Everyone was warm and welcoming.
Good Sushi and very friendly staff!! Had a good time!

I just moved to area and was surprised at how good it was... Probably some of the freshest sushi I've ever had. I got the sushi platter for 1 to go which comes with a variety of sushi and sashimi, 1 roll, and soup or salad - the sashimi was melt-in-your-mouth fresh and the entire platter was delicious. Usually take-out sushi doesn't taste as good as when you're sitting down (maybe that's just me), but it was unbelievably good. I've had it 3 times since then and will continue to keep going!
Honestly a real shock how the food quality was such a high grade in taste and presentation considering it was a local restaurant. Really worth a visit.
My favorite Asian food place in this locale.  Such great food! Everything from the menu was delicious, the waiters were awesome!! Will be back.

This is a disappointed review I have to write. We been loyal customers at Ten for the past 3 years and often take our business dinners here. Our dog a small 3 lb yorkie had enjoy outdoor dinner with us here on many occasions within these past years. However, today is a different story. We asked to be seated outdoor/patio because we had our dog, got seated, our server (a male) took out drink order, few minutes later another server (female) came out and said no dogs allow and we can't stay. We are very upset because we came in with a dog, if u r a "no dog allow" outdoor/patio restaurant then why seated customers. In addition, this is Park slope...this restaurant is no longer have our business.
Food and service are reliably good. Also good value
Neighbors restaurant, visited every week, friendly n fancy food ！

I figured I would try a new place in area...why did I wait 25 minutes? The foods is decent but the wait staff is seriously lacking in etiquette.  Two other waitresses asked for our order... after we ordered. It took over 30 minutes for mushroom soup to arrive.  I had to ask the waitress not to remove empty plated over my shoulder,  she then later reached across my plate to change chopsticks,  which I had to ask for, after having to ask for my salad before my sashimi.  I told her to hold fish until after I'm finished my salad... which arrived after my dumplings. I was told that all wait staff wait on everyone.  Disorganized staff. Bill $92 plus

A good selection of sushi, sake and appetizers. The waiters are nice and prices are fair bit the food is only four star. Some of the rolls are good but some not that much. The pork dumplings are very tasty, though. Peak times you might have to wait a little.
Great sushi.
it was ok. they had a nice happy hour but they prefer you to buy food.
Lunch bentos are delicious and you get a lot for 10 bucks!
Food is fresh, fast & tasty!! Ordered twice in the same day!!
Wonderful ambiance & the presentation of the food is beautiful.
Some of the best Japanese food I've ever had. Wonderful ambiance. Good for date or family.

A solid Sushi restaurant in the area. The staff were extremely great, helpful, and attentive. The sushi roll I ordered was much larger than I anticipated. The Kani salad is one of my favorite things to eat at sushi restaurants and they made a pretty well balanced one. My only issue was the Chicken Katsu was a little off for me. It was a bit dry and tasteless. Overall, food was good and service was good. Definitely recommend
Consistently high quality, and very nicely displayed. Always new and tempting daily specials as well.
Good food nice place for a meal
Consistently solid delivery; warm atmosphere and better food in person.  Not the best sushi in NY, but certainly one of the best in the area.
Good lunch special
Great lunch and staff. Food was fresh. Will go back when in Brooklyn.
Awesome food!
Park slopes second best sushi restaurant.. which is pretty good!
Fresh sushi and low carb options (riceless rolls)
Good sushi, but of a wait though.
Consistent quality and great lunch specials
Fun.
Go to place for sushi in park slope. Fresh and quality.
(Translated by Google) Very good food, excellent desserts, good service and adequate prices.  (Original) Muy buena comida, excelentes postres, buen servicio y precios adecuados.

If you're looking for an excellent dining experience, this is the place. Restaurant decor is thoughtfully designed with attention to detail. The food is reasonably priced and pleasingly plated. Wait staff is friendly and efficient. An overall pleasant dining experience.
below average neighborhood sushi - good for feeding kids or a quick cheapish bite
Outstanding Japanese food with a really helpful staff. Would recommend to anyone that loves good Japanese.
Nice ambiance with some outdoor seating available. The hibachi and sushi were both pretty tasty but not out of this world.

Great sushi, great service, great prices for NY. The sushi is fresh and well prepared. The tempura is flavorful and battered perfectly. The Udon broth is homemade and full of flavor. The tempura Udon is a great deal because you get a great vegetable Udon with a nice side of tempura (they don't put it in the soup where it can get all soggie). Great atmosphere as well.
Best sushi I ever been in my life. Great service, recommend it so much!
Unusual combinations stand out. Not your run of mill sushi

Nasty non-fresh food! I don't know what happened to this place lately, but their food has severely gone down. I used to love this place and get food all the time. Now, the sushi doesn't taste fresh, there's no flavor, tempura tastes like it was fried yesterday, and some of the staff has changed and the newer ones are very rude! Avoid this place ...its not worth it anymore!

Stopped in here one Saturday afternoon for a late lunch and enjoyed the chicken kushiyaki and beef maki. It was my first time dining here and I loved that I had a choice between sidewalk service and the chic interior. Love the decor and vibe, definitely good for a date night.  Note: If you're like me and love Japanese-style food but not seafood, you'll find limited options here.
wtf. this sashima was unreasonably good for 12 bucks. so fresh.  100 dollar sushi might be better, but most 20 dollar sushi is 5 times worse
Sushi Sashimi combo is my jam

Great neighborhood sushi restaurant - cozy place, friendly waiters and reasonably priced sushi. Had the peanut avocado roll as well as the vegetable naruto roll. Both are highly recommended for vegetarians!

Do not order the udon under any circumstances. Udon is a simple dish, so it is exceedingly hard to make it really well if you are not willing to put in the time. We ordered chicken and beef udon and found them both to be almost tasteless. The beef was woefully overcooked, the vegetables as well... It would have been barely acceptable if not for the unmerited $14 price tag per serving, which honestly just highlighted the mediocrity of the entire meal. I have had decent sushi from Ten, maybe they should just concentrate on that and leave the rest alone. That way they can provide a good product at an affordable price without having these sad dips in quality.

Ordered sushi take out the other night from Ten and found it to be bland and tasteless! Really, no taste at all. You'ed be much better off ordering from the place over on 7th and 4th street across from John J HS. its cheeper, tastes better and they always seem to have an A in the window. Ten gets a Five in my book . Really has gone down hill in the last year. This from someone who has grown up in NY and has eaten fresh fish all his life.  Mike
We had a lovely time here on a beautiful summer evening.  I really like that you can order tempura by the piece!
I love this restaurant!!!! Very very good sushi.  And their happy hour deals are amazing!  $5 for all cocktails.  Must try!
Great presentation and decor. Server had minimal menu knowledge and slow service but very accommodating none the less. Not to mention the amazing sizeable drinks.
Very good lunch specials.

My favorite uber-local sushi joint.  The sushi is always tasty, seems fresh and never breaks the bank.  Nice crowds every evening speaks to the restaurant's popularity amongst the locals.  Service has always been spot-on.

This might just be Park Slope's best kept secret. They do a fantastic omakase, the staff is kind and decor is quietly elegant, and the price is decent considering the quality of the fish. You'll pay a bit more than some of the places nearby, but it's worth it. The only place I've ever seen two types of eel on the menu! Mmm, eel...
